However, the one who stepped up to defend this person…

130
00:08:39,930 --> 00:08:43,350
就像你说的 我们都知道节目内容了 所以一点意思都没有
As you said, it isn't that interesting since we know everything.

131
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:46,890
这个节目总有让人惊讶的地方 所以不要放松警惕
They always surprise us with something, so don't let your guard down.

132
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:50,690
辩护律师已经退出该案件
The defense counsel had resigned from this case…

133
00:08:50,770 --> 00:08:51,820
比如像现在这个场面？
Something like that?

134
00:08:52,730 --> 00:08:53,940
确实让人惊讶啊
It is rather surprising.

135
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:57,780
这个卷发好像很眼熟啊
This is a silhouette that looks awfully familiar.

136
00:08:57,900 --> 00:08:59,110
那是什么呢
What is that?

137
00:08:59,610 --> 00:09:00,910
等一下
Look.

138
00:09:00,990 --> 00:09:03,120
你不是说不接受采访吗
I thought you weren't going to do the interview.

139
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:05,200
白实习 保持安静 让我看看我都说了什么
Ms. Baek, be quiet. I have to watch how I did.

140
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:09,920
我的声音怎么那样 原本很好听的啊
What's up with my voice? I usually have a really nice voice.

141
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:12,290
-对 -为什么要变声处理啊
-Yes. -Why did they change my voice?

142
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:14,750
唉唷 真是烦人
Gosh. That is so annoying.

143
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:17,510
如果你好奇 请给我五百韩元 如果你担心某件事 请给我一千韩元
If you're curious, it's 500 won. If you're worried, it's 1,000 won.

144
00:09:18,010 --> 00:09:19,260
看那个 五百韩元
Did you hear that? 500 won.

145
00:09:19,340 --> 00:09:21,340
如果你好奇 请给我五百韩元 是我即兴发挥的
I ad-libbed "If you're curious, it's 500 won."

146
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:23,850
你真聪明啊 口才不错
That was pretty clever. You're good at it.

147
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,730
但是
However,

148
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,350
身在看守所的金敏宰
we received a letter from Mr. Kim Minjae

149
00:09:31,690 --> 00:09:34,020
给我们写了一封信
who is in a detention center.

150
00:09:34,730 --> 00:09:37,900
这封信指引我们去往一个地方
This letter directed us to a location.

151
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:39,780
就是那个
That's it.

152
00:09:39,860 --> 00:09:43,330
那么我们在那里会找到什么呢
What do you think we found at that location?

153
00:09:44,950 --> 00:09:48,330
虽然十分令人惊讶 但我们找到了一把刀
Shockingly, it was a knife.

154
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:50,500
刀？
A knife?

155
00:09:56,840 --> 00:10:00,130
并且他在信的结尾这样写道
And he wrote this at the end of his letter,

156
00:10:00,590 --> 00:10:03,510
我承认所有罪行并愿意接受处罚
"I admit to committing everything and I'll pay for my crimes.

157
00:10:04,350 --> 00:10:07,470
我希望这把刀能成为 解决这个案件的
I hope this knife is used as the definitive evidence

158
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:09,140
决定性证据
in solving this case."

159
00:10:14,060 --> 00:10:16,570
电视台刚寄过来的
The broadcasting company just sent this over.

160
00:10:16,980 --> 00:10:17,940
好的
Okay.

161
00:10:22,910 --> 00:10:24,370
真是有意思啊
How interesting.

162
00:10:24,450 --> 00:10:26,740
他竟然亲自上交犯罪凶器
He personally presented the murder weapon.

163
00:10:28,330 --> 00:10:29,950
马上把它送到国科搜
Please send this to NFS.

164
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:31,500
-好的 -谢谢
-Yes, sir. -Thank you.

165
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,710
这把刀应该是在犯罪过程中 使用的凶器吧
Are we sure it's the knife that was used in the murder?

166
00:10:36,290 --> 00:10:37,630
我们马上就会知道了
We'll find out very soon.

